<br>
I'm sure you didn't mean for this to sound as ridiculous as it does. <br>
<br>
For one: Role playing wasn't born when Gary Gygax published a book. Role playing is playing. <br>
It's easier when you're a kid, because you get recess and stuff, and playing with Lego guys is your work. It gets more complicated as a teen or adult -- more rules, usually a lot more math, weirder people --  but still fun.<br>
<br>
You're wrong when it comes to D&amp;D-style roleplaying. EQ, no matter what server, but especially FV, is hundreds of times more dynamic than the typical D&amp;D campaign. If I never had to look up another hit point or damage thingy from a chart I'd be happy. The personalities you meet in EQ, not to mention the lore, and the energy that goes with the game (message boards, for example<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), add to it even more.<br>
<br>
I can understand pining for the old days. (D&amp;D, Boot Hill, Top Secret, Aftermath(!), the Morrow Project anyone? -- make some of that coolness into an online game...). But I don't buy broad generalizations about something as nebulous as roleplaying.<br>
<br>
Halus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.alienexplorer.com/clipart/images5/wolf.pawprint2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 6:57:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Roleplaying's in dire straits</span><hr size=1> Darn, I saw &quot;Dire Straits&quot; and thought it was another music thread.  :P<br>
