Not their best work, but I had to think quickly...<br>
<br>
2) EQ is as role playing as you want it to be, IMHO. I am somewhat new to this as EQ is my first RP game, but I have been in a Blood Bowl League for several years. For those of you not familiar, it is a Games Workshop/Warhammer tabletop creation. Think what a rugby/football match would be if played between Orcs and Wood Elves, or Halflings and the Undead, etc. Players can be killed, accumulate experience points, etc. I was never exposed to AD&amp;D as a youth, but the friends I play BB with had/have an exhaustive campaign on the old Greyhawk world. This game can be played by writing names on a roster and playing, but we have taken it several steps deeper, including writeups on the lives of our players, their personalities and background, etc. It is set in the old D&amp;D Greyhawk world. We started this league in 1996, and when these guys get killed (it does happen in-game) there are times we have to halt the game for a a few minutes to take it in. My point here is that my friends and I don't just heap our players with the best skills as they gain experience, we try to think about what would make sense for the character as well. A hard bitten human lineman, a former combat infantry sargent with a nasty disposition and a mother hen mentality toward his players would not acquire a side-step agility skill for example. So it is possible to RP in any environment. I role play an enthusiastic employee here at work, for another example.<br>
